OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784789276
OL,3,CJune heatwave cost UK economy more
OL,4,Cthan #1bn, research suggests
OL,6,FThe heatwave marked the second of
OL,7,Fthree to hit western Europe in just
OL,8,Fthree months this year, causing
OL,9,Fescalating impacts on health,
OL,10,Finfrastructure, water resources,
OL,11,Ffarming and wildlife.
OL,13,FThe average reported reduction in
OL,14,Fhours worked across the last week of
OL,15,FJune in the UK was 0.47 hours,
OL,16,Faccording to a survey analysis led by
OL,17,Fthe London School of Economics'
OL,18,FGrantham Research Institute on Climate
OL,19,FChange and the Environment and the
OL,20,FEuro-Mediterranean Centre on Climate
OL,21,FChange (CMCC).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784789276
OL,3,CJune heatwave cost UK economy more
OL,4,Cthan #1bn, research suggests
OL,6,FFor the study, published on Thursday,
OL,7,Fthe researchers asked a nationally
OL,8,Frepresentative sample of 1,950 British
OL,9,Fadults about how the heatwave affected
OL,10,Fworking hours, ability to sleep and
OL,11,Fany changes to their working routine
OL,12,Fduring the week.
OL,14,FThe team estimated the economic cost
OL,15,Fof lost output driven by the heatwave
OL,16,Fbased on the workers' responses about
OL,17,Fadjustments they had to make.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784789276
OL,3,CJune heatwave cost UK economy more
OL,4,Cthan #1bn, research suggests
OL,6,FThey found that those working in
OL,7,Fphysically demanding jobs that are
OL,8,Fmore highly exposed to heat in sectors
OL,9,Fsuch as construction and agriculture
OL,10,Freduced their hours by more than those
OL,11,Fworking in low-exposure and physically
OL,12,Fundemanding jobs such as academia.
OL,14,FFindings from the survey also show
OL,15,F3.6% of respondents ` equivalent to
OL,16,Fapproximately 1.25 million workers in
OL,17,Fthe population ` did not work at all
OL,18,Fthat week because of the heat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
